27/07/2004
BRUSSELS, Belgium -- During a meeting with NATO Secretary General Jaap de Hoop Scheffer on Monday (26 July), Macedonian President Branko Crvenkovski urged the Alliance and the EU to provide more concrete support for Macedonia's Euro-Atlantic integration efforts. 
Crvenkovski and de Hoop Scheffer also discussed intensifying reforms within the Action Plan for the country's membership in NATO, as well as activities related to the controversial decentralisation process. 
(MIA, A1 TV - 26/07/04)
